# Personal Claude Code Preferences (NOT committed to git)
# Copy this to CLAUDE.local.md and customize

# Response style
- Respond in English
- Be concise — skip explanations I didn't ask for
- When writing code, add brief inline comments for complex logic only
- Show me the full file when creating new files, diffs when editing

# Dev environment
- I use pnpm (not npm or yarn)
- I use VS Code / Cursor as my primary editor
- My terminal is iTerm2 / Windows Terminal
- Docker Desktop is running for local Postgres and Redis

# Testing preference
- Write tests alongside the implementation, not separately
- Use descriptive test names: "should [expected behavior] when [condition]"
- Prefer integration tests over mocking everything

# Git preference
- Create small, focused commits
- Use conventional commit messages
- I'll review the diff before committing
